The paper discusses the development and evaluation of machine learning and artificial intelligence algorithms for human-aware navigation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The dataset is designed to evaluate the robots' ability to assess the level of discomfort that their presence might generate among humans, which involves analyzing human behavior and emotions, potentially falling under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
